# Pull Request Naming Convention

Pull Request titles must follow the same format as commit messages for consistency.

## Format

```
<type>(<optional-scope>): <short imperative description>
```

## Allowed Types

| Type     | Description                                          |
| -------- | ---------------------------------------------------- |
| feat     | New feature or enhancement                           |
| fix      | Bug fix                                              |
| refactor | Code refactoring that doesn't change behavior        |
| docs     | Documentation-only changes                           |
| chore    | Maintenance tasks (e.g. packaging, dependencies)     |
| perf     | Performance improvements                             |
| style    | Code style or formatting changes (no logic impact)   |
| ci       | CI/CD pipeline changes                               |

## Rules

- **Use imperative mood**: "Add…", "Fix…", "Update…" (not "Added", "Fixed", "Updated")
- **Keep it under ~70 characters**
- **Include issue/ticket IDs when applicable**: `fix(#42): handle null token values`
- **Avoid "WIP" in titles**: Use draft PRs instead
- **Use lowercase**: Type and scope should be lowercase

## Branch Prefixes vs PR Title Types

Branch prefixes (`feature/`, `chore/`, `hotfix/`) are for branch organization and differ from PR title types:

- Branch `feature/add-card-component` → PR title: `feat(components): add Card component`
- Branch `chore/update-dependencies` → PR title: `chore(deps): update tsup to v9`
- Branch `hotfix/fix-broken-export` → PR title: `fix(tokens): export missing color variable`

**PR titles use commit message types (`feat`, `fix`, `chore`), not branch prefixes (`feature/`, `hotfix/`).**

## GitHub's Auto-Suggested Titles

**GitHub auto-suggests titles based on branch names. These do NOT follow our convention — always rewrite them.**

- ❌ `Feature/add card component` → ✅ `feat(components): add Card component`
- ❌ `Chore/update dependencies` → ✅ `chore(deps): update tsup to v9`

## Common Scopes

| Scope      | Example                                          | Description                |
| ---------- | ------------------------------------------------ | -------------------------- |
| components | `feat(components): add Card component`           | React components           |
| tokens     | `fix(tokens): export missing color variable`     | Design tokens              |
| brand      | `chore(brand): add project mark assets`          | Static brand artwork (`src/brand/`) |
| favicons   | `feat(favicons): add gtmt favicon bundle`        | Favicon bundles            |
| styles     | `fix(styles): correct reset specificity`         | Global styles/CSS          |
| hooks      | `feat(hooks): add useMediaQuery hook`            | Shared React hooks         |
| utils      | `refactor(utils): simplify color helpers`        | Helpers and constants      |
| deps       | `chore(deps): update tsup to v9`                 | Dependency management      |

## Examples

- `feat(components): add Card component with outlined variant`
- `fix(tokens): export missing surface color token`
- `docs: update contributing guide`
- `chore: update tsup to v9`
- `ci: add publish workflow for GitHub Packages`
- `fix(#42): handle null token values`

## Guidelines

- **One logical change per PR**
- **Be descriptive** — the title should clearly describe what the PR does
- **Match commit messages** — PR titles follow the same format as commit messages
- **Review before submitting** — always rewrite GitHub's auto-suggested title
